text.text:
almost 50mins and still waiting….the place is not even full. it is unable to handle surge at meal times. if i have known the long wait, i would give it a miss…

if u wish to patronise during lunch, be ready to wait at least 45-60mins.

will provide food review after i managed to eat it. haha…

total wait was 55mins for a fish and chips. taste was average. texture was good. salad veg was too hard and i wasted them all.

overall, my friends and i agreed that we would likely not patronise again.

I wont recommended to anyone to eat here…

Wanting to go there to gather and have fun and chill. No staff entertain us and who is the staff? Seated ourselves to a table, then no one is there to serve us, 30mins noone.

Went to the counter, all busy talking. Stand there for 10 mins, like I'm a glass, all talking to themselves.

Staff only talks to regular customers, looks like only serve Regulars. Continue lo

BTW, we left.

Will I come here again? Never

text.text: We were excited when we found a highly rated yet reasonably priced place which serves food that the adults and kids like to eat on Google that is near our house. However, the experience was way below our expectations. The atmosphere was too dark and furnishings seemed cheap looking. Storage of beer barrels was everywhere. Staff was playing darts. They couldnt really communicate well and customer service was sub par at most. After all this, we were putting all our hopes and dreams into their food. Alas, it was all such a great letdown, to the point where my my kids were also "pushing" me to give a rating for this place. Maybe we were too excited.....but i won't patronize this place again. If i do (i won't), probably for a jug Tiger after a hard day's work.

text.text: Found this most amazing chillax place after a reno ID visit around the area. It is pretty near to jurong east mrt and has great food, music and atmosphere. The alcoholic drinks are at a great bargain (29.90 for yakult soju, or 1 pint of beer at 7.90), and the food is amazing. I visited 3 times and all these times did not disappoint. On my most recent visit, ordered the bbq food and sat outside enjoying the 90s chinese ktv songs. The best is that this place is not crowded over the weekends, so you can really sit and relax over the whole evening and comfortably chat over a few drinks. The staffs are friendly and attentive, which i must say it is a real pleasure and delight dining there! Must try!

text.text: Surprisingly to find the food here was really good. The pull pork burger, the pork chop, beef cube rice bowl and prawn Aglio Olio. The beer is reasonable price with 9+ per pint! Under the mrt track with outdoor and in door sitting. You can play the dart inside and it was quite a great hangout place !
